      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/discretization-error-level2",
      "rationale": "A systematic grid convergence index (GCI) study was performed using three mesh refinement levels (3.2M, 8.7M, and 21.4M cells). The GCI for the hemolysis index QoI was 2.1% on the fine mesh, well within the 5% acceptance threshold. Richardson extrapolation confirms monotonic convergence. Achieved level 3 exceeds required level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/test-conditions-level2",
      "rationale": "Experimental validation test conditions (flow rate, rotational speed, blood analog viscosity, temperature) were matched to CFD boundary conditions within documented tolerances. Five operating points spanning the clinical CPB flow range (2–6 L/min, 2400–3600 RPM) were replicated. Test condition uncertainty is quantified and reported in the UQ annex."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/output-comparison-level2",
      "rationale": "CFD-predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) values were compared against experimental measurements at all five operating points. Mean absolute error was 8.3% with 95% confidence bounds computed via bootstrap resampling. Systematic bias was assessed and found non-significant (p=0.31). Achieved level 3 reflects quantitative uncertainty-aware comparison exceeding the required level 2 qualitative agreement standard."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/qoi-relevance-level2",
      "rationale": "The primary QoI is the normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) and the derived relative hemolysis index (RH). Both quantities directly map to the regulatory acceptance criterion (RH < 1 vs. predicate device). Clinical relevance is established by linkage to ISO 10993-4 hemolysis testing standards and FDA hemolysis guidance. QoI relevance is confirmed at required level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
