      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/validation-relevance-level2",
      "rationale": "Validation activities were conducted on the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry under CPB-representative operating conditions using a validated blood analog fluid (glycerol-water mixture per ASTM F1841). The validation domain overlaps the COU operating envelope across all five flow-speed combinations. Geometric similarity between validation and COU configurations is documented. Relevance level 2 is achieved and meets the requirement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
