      "rationale": "Model input parameters (blood viscosity, density, pump geometry tolerances) are sourced from ISO 10993-4 and manufacturer specifications with documented uncertainty ranges. Sensitivity of NIH to ±5% variation in viscosity was assessed via parametric runs and found to be less than 3%. Formal model inputs factor assessment is scoped out at MRL 2 with sensitivity analysis documented as supporting evidence."
